AD|Gifted - Introducing the new Graco Foldlite Travel Cot! üí´ 

We have been testing out the new Graco lightweight travel cot that is quick and easy to assemble for various uses such as travelling away from home, visiting family, and a place for your little one to stay in while you get some housework done (Dante is obsessed with trying to wrestle the hoover üòÇ)

The instructions to assemble and put away are very simple to follow, and it helps that the travel cot is light (6.78kg - 30% lighter than other Graco travel cots) I am almost 30 weeks pregnant so it was essential I have something easy to set up and manoeuvre. This will also come in extra handy for when our new baby makes an appearance.

The cot has two folds, the first being the ‚ÄòHome Fold‚Äô which makes storing it next to the sofa ideal. The ‚ÄòTravel Fold‚Äô is an even more compact fold for when you want to take it in the car, using very little room.

The price tag is ¬£100 and I personally feel the quality is worth it. For such a light weight piece of equipment it is durable and sturdy giving peace of mind your little one is in a safe space.

This is our first Graco product and we are over the moon with it. Have you tried any of the Graco range?

@graco_uk @officialparentsquad 

#gracouk #gracohomeandaway #gracofoldlite #gracosidebyside #parentsquad

node.text:
Almost 34 Weeks Pregnant ü§∞üèª‚ú® 

I feel cool as a cucumber, when I probably should be anxious as anything! I‚Äôm soon going to be going through all that pain again to bring another little life into the world and into our loving embrace as a family. I can‚Äôt wait to see Dante become a big brother, and watch them grow up playing together. I can picture the mischief they will get up to already. 

I had a really bad birth with Dante, that I still physically suffer from so I‚Äôm crossing my fingers this time around it goes faster and I don‚Äôt have to have an episiotomy üò© I couldn‚Äôt walk for so long and the recovery process is so slow. But this is our last baby, and so I know I will get back to normal soon enough. I‚Äôm not panicking about what to take to hospital with me, and I‚Äôm not over thinking anything because literally the birth plan and every other bit of organisation goes out the window when you get into it üòÜ 

I love my pregnancy bump but honestly I can‚Äôt wait to have my body back to how it was and actually being able to sleep on my front again üòÑ

Not only can you plan your months, but there are separate pages for goals, life visions, missions, affirmations, habits and skills, vision boards, mind maps, monthly reviews and weekly pages üìñ 

They also have a range of budget and expenses books, meal planners, food journals, financial books, gratitude and lots of sticker packs!

You can use my code FOXXIEFAMILY for 10% off their website (currently only US citizens can use this)

For all other parts of the world, please find them on Amazon UK, Amazon EU, and Amazon US via global shipping üì¶ ‚ú®

node.text:
AD|Gifted - Johnson‚Äôs Baby Products üßº 

We were kindly sent some Johnson‚Äôs baby bottles which consisted of Shampoo, Lotion, and baby oil. We have used the shampoo previously and love the smell and softness it leaves Dante‚Äôs hair with. The lotion left Dante‚Äôs skin so soft and we used a little of the oil for a back massage which relaxed him just before bedtime. We had never tried the lotion or oil before which was great because it expanded our knowledge on what products work best for us.

What I really like is that Johnson‚Äôs has teamed up with Alder Hey Children‚Äôs Hospital once again to raise money for funding family integrated care rooms üíó . Last year, Johnson‚Äôs helped them raise ¬£83,733 for a brand new surgical neonatal unit which is incredible! It‚Äôs so important to be able to keep families together in a safe space. It shows that they really do keep families at the heart of everything üôå üè• 

Johnson‚Äôs will donate 5p for each Alder Hey Limited Edition product purchased and these bottles are available in Asda, Tesco, Boots and Superdrug. This is an amazing charity to get behind as Alder Hey is one of the biggest and busiest children‚Äôs hospital in Europe and they really need support. Let‚Äôs do our bit and help improve the services available for families üíï üë∂üèº

Many thanks @officialparentsquad and @johnsonsbabyuk üíù

node.text:
Wooden Toys üôå

I never dreamed I would own any wooden toys. The thought of them flying at my head was enough to convince me not to have any for Dante. But then I read that William and Kate had predominantly wooden toys in their children‚Äôs playroom. They claimed that it helped with their hand-eye coordination and imagination. Well, that was enough to peak my interest.

@bigjigstoys were kind enough to send us the Healthy Eating Food Set to try out. I was pleasantly surprised to see Dante drop his attention from the tv to come and sit with me to explore the wooden shapes. I can honestly say this was the first time I felt like we properly played together, with him handing me different fruits and then taking the bread and cheeses from me. He didn‚Äôt attempt to throw any of them, but did sink his teeth into the banana and egg (his two favourite foods!). 

The set is made from premium quality, smooth wood that‚Äôs gentle on little hands and the pieces are coated in non-toxic paints and lacquers - which is great because Dante really enjoyed chewing on them! It‚Äôs also a fun way of teaching our children about healthy foods!

The quality of the toys and boxes is beautiful, and so inexpensive. You can use my code FOXXIE10 for a nice 10% discount which makes it even more appealing! 

Do you have wooden toys for your little ones?

#bigjigstoys #bigjigs

AD|Gifted - Reading üìñ 

They say that a good book is a magical doorway to a world of adventure and possibilities ‚ú® 

I‚Äôve tried to build Dante‚Äôs collection of books so that there is always something there to stimulate his mind and learning process, but he is now at that age where he is so busy at the moment that it‚Äôs not enough my voice keeping him interested in a story.

@dittybirdbooks kindly sent us some  audio learning books that have push button pages to grab the attention of children, encourage reading, and listening to words and sounds. On the back of the books is an on/off button and has long lasting batteries so you get plenty of use out of them. Dante showed a lot more interest listening to the fun voice overs and animal noises. We have some of the new collection which consist of the 100 words, and fun musical sounds and songs.

I would definitely recommend checking these audio books out, especially if your child isn‚Äôt speaking yet. Dante doesn‚Äôt say much at the moment, but I can see these books will be a huge learning curve for him.

Thank you @dittybirdbooks for the brilliant books üìö üíô

Doesn‚Äôt he look so grown up? 

Dante loves his Amazon Fire Tablet. I know they don‚Äôt recommend children as young as him using them but I‚Äôm guilty of being a mum who just needs one to get five minutes of peace üòÆ‚Äçüí® 

I think Dante is going through a super clingy stage where he wants to be carried constantly and cuddled but every time he feels the baby kick, he gets frustrated. 

At least the tablet can provide him with a little distraction and he already knows how to get YouTube up and pick which Bing video he wants. This tablet will also make boring car journeys a lot more tolerable for him.

One of the best features is the protective thick case it comes in. The amount of times it‚Äôs been dropped on the floor or hit against the wall ! üôà it also comes with a 2 year warranty which is very handy.

We were lucky to get ours in the Amazon Prime Sale for half price and it‚Äôs worth every penny. 

Do you have a tablet for your little one?

AD|Gifted - PAMPERS üí´ 

NEW Stop & Protect pocket‚Ñ¢ with up to 12 hours of all-around leakage and protection.

Pampers new Stop & Protect pocket‚Ñ¢ helps prevent unwanted leaks at the back. The 360-degree fit stretches to ensure there are no gaps for unwanted leaks as well as double layered cuffs and a super absorbent core offering up to 12 hours of all-round leakage protection so you and your family can enjoy even more time together without the constant interruption of nappy changing üëå 

Now, as most of know, we are a cloth bum family and have been cloth nappy-ing exclusively for just over a year. But recently my low blood pressure is taking its toll with being almost 33 weeks pregnant, so trying to keep on top of washing cloth nappies, stuffing, and folding, has been a challenge.

When we were offered the chance to join the testing team for Pampers I saw it as a sign that I just needed to take that break. We have been using the nappies for almost a week now and it‚Äôs been so nice to have a rest, and I‚Äôm sure my washing machine has enjoyed the break too!

We used Pampers when Dante was born and with another baby soon to come, I needed to find an alternative if I was struggling to cloth two babies.

The nappies are so dainty compared to the cloth ones but wow, they really do hold in the moisture and poo. No leaks at all, even when asleep on his side üôå I also like that they are pants with a stretchy waistband so no uncomfortable sitting positions for Dante.

I would definitely recommend these nappies and will have them as my go-to when needed when my second baby comes along.

Thank you @officialparentsquad for giving us the opportunity to test these out. 
 

#pampersparents #poonami #dontfearthepoonami #parentsquad #pampers

Anyone else love a good, smelly candle?
This was my first from @imperialcandles and it smelled absolutely divine! Just a short amount of burning filled the room with its scent. 

Imperial candles not only smell great but they contain beautiful jewellery hidden inside made from gold and silver. Each candle comes with their own theme and you can choose from having a surprise necklace, ring, or earrings. You can also choose the size of your ring when selecting that choice. I also love that they are made from soy!

Which candles do you like and what are your favourite scents? üïØ
